
[1]inhospitable

   INHOS'PITABLE, a. [in and hospitable.]

   1. Not hospitable; not disposed to entertain strangers gratuitously;
   declining to entertain guests, or entertaining them with reluctance; as
   an inhospitable person or people.

   2. Affording no conveniences, subsistence or shelter to strangers; as
   inhospitable desserts or rocks.
